        "Page 1",
        "Mary Lennox was the most disagreeable child anyone had ever met. She had lived in sunny India, spoiled by servants, cross from morning till night. Then sickness came, and her parents were gone forever. Poor Mary was sent far across the sea to England, to live with an uncle she had never met. She was ten years old, thin and yellow-faced, and terribly, terribly alone."
